[normal]Written evidence from [bold]Carplus[bold] Trust [bold](TIC 060)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Carplus 
[normal]Trust 
[normal]is pleased to submit w
[normal]ritten 
[normal]evidence
[normal] to the 
[normal]inquiry on passenger transport in isolated communities by the 
[normal]Commons Select Committee on Transport
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]Carplus
[normal] was established in 2000 to support the development of car clubs and ride-sharing schemes 
[normal]throughout the UK
[normal], in response to growing environmental concerns around private car use.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Over the past decade, Carplus has played an active role in the introduction 
[normal]and growth of the car club sector in the UK. From a handful of community-led car clubs there are now over 150,000 members in England alone. These members have access to over 2000 vehicles in over 50 locations across England, Wales and Scotland.
[normal]&#xa0;
